==Latin==
===Etymology===
From [[punctum|pūnctum]] + [[temporis]] (''genitive of'' [[tempus]]); literally "point of time"
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈpuːnk.tʊm ˈtɛːm.pɔ.rɪs/}}
===Noun===
'''[[punctum|pūnctum]] [[temporis]]''' (''genitive'' '''[[puncti|pūncti]] [[temporis]]'''); {{n}}, ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin second declension|second declension]]''

# [[second]] (''unit of time'')
# [[instant]], [[moment]]

===Usage notes===
*This term appears in later Latin, after the establishment of measured time.

